nificant ‘imperial’ influence across generations of writers and diverse types of historical text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImperialismxHistoriography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritain.  aEmpire.  aHistoriography.  aImperial.  aInterpretations.  aUnited Kingdom.1 ade Groot, Joanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611097840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526110978423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526110978/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles